            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ο̄</orig>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>Intraduisible.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Intraducibile.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمة بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>As final letter omicron might correspond to later <foreign xml:lang="grc">ο</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="grc">ω</foreign>. Unless a pronominal ending
                of singular neutral (such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἄλλο</foreign>), which would be very surprising, a long o, ending of genitive singular, perhaps of a personal name,
                    seems much more plausible.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
